# API & Data Flow

This app has **no REST API layer** (`routes/api.php` is empty). Data flows through Inertia.

## Prefer: Inertia page props

Controller loads and shapes data; React renders props.

```php
return Inertia::render('organization/documents/show', [
    'document' => $document->toShowArray(),
    'can' => DocumentPagePermissions::for($request->user()),
    'back' => DocumentShowBackNavigation::resolve($request, $employee),
]);
```

Reference: `EmployeeDocumentShowController.php`

Domain queries live in `app/Support/`, not controllers:

- `DocumentBrowseQuery`, `EmployeeDirectoryQuery`, `RecentActivityQuery`

## Mutations

| Action | Pattern |
|--------|---------|
| Create/update | `useForm().post/put()` or `form.post/put()` |
| Delete | `router.delete()` or `form.delete()` |
| Filters/search | `router.get()` via `useServerPaginationFilters` |
| Partial reload | `{ only: ['document'] }` or `partialReloadKeys` prop |

## Flash messages (prefer server-side)

```php
return redirect()->route('organization.branches.index')
    ->with('success', 'Branch created.');
```

Client: `components/http-exception-toasts.tsx` shows `flash.success|error|info` on `router.on('success')`.

**Avoid** duplicate client `toast.success` in `onSuccess` when server already flashes.

## Wayfinder (prefer for new frontend code)

Generated — do not edit `resources/js/routes/` or `resources/js/actions/` manually.

```tsx
import { show as documentShow } from '@/routes/organization/documents/employee/files';
import * as EmployeeDocumentController from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/Organization/EmployeeDocumentController';

documentShow.url({ employee: id, document: docId }, { query: { from: 'profile' } });
EmployeeDocumentController.destroy.url({ employee, document });
```

Helper example: `features/organization/documents/shared/document-show-url.ts`

Legacy code still uses hardcoded paths (e.g. `'/organization/branches'`) — match surrounding file when editing; use Wayfinder in new code.

## Rare JSON / XHR

| Case | Mechanism |
|------|-----------|
| 2FA setup | `useHttp()` — `hooks/use-two-factor-auth.ts` |
| Document versions (legacy sheet) | `useHttp()` — `document-versions-sheet.tsx` |
| Master-data quick create | `ReturnsQuickCreateJson` trait |
| Downloads | `<a href>` or `StreamedResponse` |
| Webhooks | dedicated controllers |

## Avoid

- React Query / TanStack Query / SWR — not in this project.
- Axios — removed; use Inertia client or `useHttp`.
- New JSON API endpoints when Inertia visit + partial reload suffices.
